<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Boanerges on 05-01-2001 01:22 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL"> [QUOTE]Originally posted by Alliliel:
[b]I think it doesn't help that Gfaymart is *the* auction zone on Tunare.

But I have an additional problem in that I don't want to put my poor mage anyplace too dangerous since she is the one I log in when Alliliel camped out of a bad situation.

Zamora tells Feigned_Monk01 "Alliliel here! Safe to log in? That was scary!"

[/b][/QUOTE]

I know the feeling. Except on CT it's EC, not GF that gets the /auc spam. If you want to do ANYTHING besides auction you have to turn off pretty much everything.

There's a problem with GF... it's a newbie zone for not one but 2 races, both of which are quite popular. And it's no different on CT. Having started a HE and a WE character, I know it's no picnic. I remember when I was working my druid up at orc hill (next to Keletin). EVERYONE congregates there. And for some odd reason, twinks abound there. My own druid was twinked a bit but nowhere near as bad as some. I went head to head with a level 8 WE warrior in full bronze wielding a YK. I was beating an orc in front of one of the isolated tents in the valley and he came up and began to bang away. Of course, he was a fool to think a melee could KS a caster. I laid in with nukes and got the kill and I chewed him out for his blatant attempt to KS and was met with "I was here first". Whatever.

My suggestion to you and anyone else thinking of making a light elf twink... move somewhere else. In your case, Ali, I'd move to Tox. Most of the serious twinks go to Qeynos to level up leaving mostly true newbies. There's TONS of room, lots to kill and as an extra bonus for your mage you have the benefit of the Erudin library to buy some of the harder to find mage spells (Heatstone, weapon summons, waterstone, etc).

One out of level 9 stuff, head to Steamfont near the mino caves. EVERYTHING is blue and soloing is a snap and you can sail to 15 or so. Then hit Unrest a bit or Lake Omen to work up to 30 (Lake not too bad on CT since it's wide open and I find my mage can solo or group at will). Be warned that Unrest has a level gap between 17 and 20 where yard trash greens but the house is still red.

In short, no, Alliliel, you're not short tempered, you just found a lot of short (brained) people  ;)

------------------
Boanerges Thundercry
Erudite Templar of Prexus
Cohort Chalybeius
Cazic Thule Server</TEXTAREA>
